Here's the HTML code in JSON format using JavaScript objects to represent the HTML elements:

```json
{
  "element": "div",
  "children": [
    {
      "element": "p",
      "attributes": {
        "class": "link"
      },
      "children": [
        {
          "element": "span",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "  |  "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Alternatively, if you want to represent the HTML code in a more simplified JSON format, you could use a string-based representation:

```json
{
  "html": "<p class=\"link\"><span>  |  </span></p>"
}
```

Or if you prefer an array-based format using a more normalized structure:

```json
{
  "tag": "div",
  "class": null,
  "children": [
    {
      "tag": "p",
      "class": "link",
      "children": [
        {
          "tag": "span",
          "class": null,
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "  |  "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```